But yeah that's what I've got going so far! I'm hoping tweeting this and getting some attention will get me more into the idea of actually writing more, lol.
She also prefers the company of animals (and machines) to people mostly cause home life was not that great for her (due to how difficult it is for to speak.)

Personality wise because Chrono doesn't talk she comes off as cold and easily annoyed. Most people have their headcanon about her and she's fine with that. 

Mostly she's just very catlike. Not very affectionate until she gets to know a person, sleeps frequently (and anywhere).

Other:

-No, Chrono is not her real name. It's a title of sorts.
-The former bearer of the name was someone she trusted (not so much any more.)
-The bearer of the name is compelled to look for an entity known as the "Dead Queen"...

The setting: 

-A desert backdrop with post apocalyptic stylings courtesy of the aftermath of a battle between man and machines.
-Humanity is just starting to get back on it's feet
-Some modern conveniences but these are rare.

-She's of Filipino decent
-Doesn't like talking much because she's admittedly bad at it.
-Because of this she's quite expressive (which I hope comes through on these.)
-She's a wanderer who likes tinkering on machines and building things out of scrap.

Details are, well, admittedly scant because heh I'm not in a super good place mentally atm so planning/writing has come to a standstill. 

That being said I can at least throw ya'll some breadcrumbs!
